    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix incorrect packet size calculation in OTG traffic generator\n\n### Summary\nThe OTG traffic generator in the OpenAirInterface 5G codebase contained an issue with the `size_dist()` function that caused unexpected packet size behavior when using FIXED distribution types. The problem occurred because the function was unnecessarily applying `ceil()` to integer values, which could lead to type conversion issues and inconsistent behavior.\n\nUnder certain traffic configurations, this resulted in packet sizes that were larger than expected, causing buffer overflows in the PDCP layer during high-throughput simulations.\n\nThe issue was particularly noticeable when running M2M traffic scenarios with FIXED packet size distributions, where packets would occasionally exceed the maximum allowed size of 1500 bytes.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/UTIL/OTG/otg_tx.c`: Removed unnecessary `ceil()` calls for integer values in FIXED, VIDEO, and BACKGROUND_DIST cases in both `time_dist()` and `size_dist()` functions.\n\n"
}